sentences: Bohdana Froliak (or Bohdana Frolyak; born 5 May 1968 in Vydyniv, Ivano-Frankivsk Oblast, Ukrainian SSR) is a modern Ukrainian composer.
In 1986, she graduated from Solomiya Krushelnytska Lviv Musical School after studying piano, music theory and composition.
In 1991, she graduated from Lviv Conservatory as a composer.
In 1998, Frolyak completed a non-degree postgraduate course of the same university.
In 2009, she attended two courses at the faculty of composition and faculty of contemporary music and jazz of Academy of Music in Kraków (Poland).
Since 1991 she has been a lecturer at faculty of musical composition at Lviv Conservatory.
